All the parchaa api's are secured by the client_credentials auth method and for getting
these client credentials you need to contact parchaa administrators. after getting these
credentials you have to make a call which returns access_token which is bearer token and
this bearer token is used for al the API's of parchaa.


### Request Information
|Category|Value|
|-----------|--------|
|Http request| `POST`|
|URL| https://api.parchaa.com/token |

### Headers
|Key|Value|
|-------------------|----------------------|
|Content-Type| application/x-www-form-urlencoded |

This header is must to pass while requesting for token

### Request Parameters in Body

We need to pass these parameters in request body as x-www-form-urlencoded

|Key|Value|
|----------|--------|
|grant_type*|client_credentials|
|client_id*|Your Client ID|
|client_secret*|Your Client Secret|
|scope| Scope|

Note: grant type will be "client_credentials" which will be constant and replace
the client_id and client_secret values with the one which are being provided by Parchaa.
And * represent Required field

scope
Can be a combination of any custom scopes associated with an app client.
 Any scope that you request must be activated for the app client, or Amazon
 Cognito will ignore it. If the client doesn't request any scopes, the authentication
 server uses all custom scopes associated with the client.

Optional. Only used if the grant_type is client_credentials.

